claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: Two stacked line plots showing cumulative incidence (y-axis, logarithmic scale from 0.0001 to 0.02) versus time (CDC-ILI Date from January to April 2008) with a red solid curve and a blue dashed curve in each plot. The figure shows cumulative incidence curves over time but does not provide any information about vaccine production methods, mutations during production, or vaccine effectiveness. It does not support the claim. Note: The image is clear enough to see axes and colored curves, but no labels or annotations reference cell- or egg-based production or mutation data.
